Another explosion has rocked Nukkai, a suburb of Jalingo barely three days after an explosion occurred at International Cattle Market Iware, in Taraba. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that it happened when the entire town was in a blackout due to power outage. Mr Hassan Danzumi, an eye witness close to the area, said that several people were injured, but no life was lost. Taraba police spokesman, DSP Abdullahi Usman who confirmed the incident said nine people were injured and couldnâ€™t confirm any casualty.